act.article:
2 Definitions.—In these rules, unless the context otherwise requires,—
a ‘Act’ means the Bureau of Indian Standards Act, 1986 (63 of 1986);
b ‘Form’ means a Form appended to the Schedule to these rules;
c ‘Ministry’ means the Ministry of Civil Supplies, Consumer Affairs and Public Distribution; and
d ‘Principal Officer’in relation to a consumer association means any individual who is specifically authorised in writing or by means of a resolution adopted by such consumer association in that behalf.
